Michael Krupp, a Golden, Colo.,businessman and major shareholder of Kappa Networks Inc, saidhe and Kappa's management are considering seeking a mergerbetween Kappa and Radiation Systems Inc.    In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,Krupp said companies he controls and Kappa acquired a combined292,000 Radiation System shares, or 5.25 pct of the total.    Krupp, who has a 24.4 pct stake in Kappa, said he and Kappamanagement believe a Kappa-Radiation Systems combination wouldbe good for both companies. But no decision has been made onwhether or how to proceed with a merger attempt, he added. Reuter&#3;